# Pull Request Readiness Check

Comprehensive pre-PR validation combining quality, architecture, and testing checks:

**Code Quality:**
- ESLint compliance (no warnings/errors)
- TypeScript strict mode compliance
- No TODO/FIXME comments in production code
- No commented-out code blocks
- No console.log/debug statements (except error logging)

**Architecture Compliance:**
- Layer separation (Component → Action → Use Case → Repository)
- No Component → Repository (must go through Action → Use Case)
- No Repository → Repository dependencies
- executePromise used for ALL external calls in Use Cases
- ClientResult pattern followed
- Proper dependency injection in Actions

**Type Organization:**
- DTO types in `*-type.ts` (exported)
- Response types in `*-repo.ts` (internal, NOT exported)
- Props types in components (local, NOT exported)

**Feature Structure:**
- Correct folder structure:
  - `actions/[feature]-actions.ts`
  - `components/[feature]-form.tsx`
  - `logic/[feature]-use-case.ts`
  - `logic/[feature]-repo.ts`
  - `logic/[feature]-type.ts`
  - `__tests__/[feature]-actions.test.ts`
  - `__tests__/[feature]-use-case.test.ts`
  - `__tests__/[feature]-test-utils.ts`

**Next.js Patterns:**
- "use client" on interactive components
- "use server" on Server Actions
- React Hook Form + Zod validation
- Proper FormData handling
- Correct redirect usage

**Testing:**
- Tests exist for new Actions and Use Cases
- Test utilities created (`*-test-utils.ts`)
- 3-4 essential test cases per function
- Tests pass locally (`npm test`)

**Error Handling:**
- Repository throws errors (no try/catch)
- Use Case wraps with executePromise
- Action returns ClientResult or redirects
- Component displays user-friendly messages

**Code Comments:**
- Comments explain WHY, not WHAT
- Business rules documented
- Security considerations noted
- No obvious code commented

Provides actionable checklist of issues to fix before creating PR.

**Agent Used:** Invokes `architecture-validator-agent`.

## Usage
```
/review-pr [file_or_directory_path]
```

## Parameters
- `file_or_directory_path`: Path to file or directory to review (required - usually `features/[feature-name]/`)
